            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;This question asks &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&quot;Why did this [the wrong way] get implemented so?&quot;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; It doesn&apos;t ask &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&quot;What&apos;s the right way?&quot;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;, which is covered by [&lt;i&gt;Why does using arg=None fix Python&apos;s mutable default argument issue?&lt;/i&gt;]*(&lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10676729/why-does-using-arg-none-fix-pythons-mutable-default-argument-issue&quot; title=&quot;why does using arg none fix pythons mutable default argument issue&quot;&gt;stackoverflow.com/questions/10676729/&lt;/a&gt;). New users are almost always less interested in the former and much more in the latter, so that&apos;s sometimes a very useful link/dupe to cite.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
