                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Normative structure is no quirk or limitation in my book. I know it can be clumsy and ugly, but you can call it a &quot;definition&quot; of something. The dynamic languages seem a bit like anarchists to me: Sure everybody is free, but you need structure to get someone to empty the trash and pave the road. Guess I&apos;m old... :)&lt;/span&gt;

